{"questionId":"9067305","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">A student synthesized aspirin, acetylsalicylic acid, in a school laboratory.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"__IMG__/af1a8f4d885f34fb3ff17759315f51472889ddf2.png\" width=\"203\" height=\"273\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">0.300 g of crude aspirin was dissolved in ethanol and titrated with sodium hydroxide solution, NaOH (aq).</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">NaOH (aq) + C<sub>9</sub>H<sub>8</sub>O<sub>4</sub> (in ethanol) → NaC<sub>9</sub>H<sub>7</sub>O<sub>4</sub> (aq) + H<sub>2</sub>O (l)</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Determine the mass of aspirin which reacted with 16.25 cm<sup>3</sup> of 0.100 mol dm<sup>−3</sup> NaOH solution.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">n(aspirin) «= n(NaOH) =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{16}}{\\text{.25 c}}{{\\text{m}}^3}}}{{1000}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>16</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>.25 c</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>m</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1000</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> × 0.100 mol dm<sup>–3</sup> » = 1.625 × 10<sup>–3</sup> «mol»&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">m(aspirin) «= 1.625 × 10<sup>–3</sup> mol × 180.17 g mol<sup>–1</sup> » = 0.293 «g»&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong> Note:</strong>&nbsp;Award <strong>[2]</strong> for correct final answer.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067305","referenceCode":"19M.3.sl.TZ2.15b(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine the mass of aspirin which reacted with 16.25 cm3 of 0.100 mol dm−3 NaOH solution.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry","D.2 Aspirin and penicillin","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}